parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deteriorating insulation on the engine wiring harness can cause electrical shorts, leading to engine stalling, fires, or crashes, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Check engine light appears
vehicle runs erratically
engine stalling
wires rubbing together
exposed bare wiring
engine shutting off while driving at high speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to surge forward or lose braking capability, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle surges forward while applying brakes
the vehicle rolls forward after coming to a stop
the brakes do not respond or are delayed
unusual sounds or noises when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Anti-lock Brake System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to lose braking capability, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Complete loss of braking
ABS system activates unnecessarily
unusual sounds or noises when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pad Wear Causing ABS Activation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Worn-out brake pads can cause the ABS system to activate unnecessarily, leading to reduced braking performance and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Front brake pads squeak
ABS system activates unnecessarily
unusual sounds or noises when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to safely secure a child seat can increase the risk of injury or fatality to children in the event of a crash, compromising their safety and well-being.
symptoms: Difficulty or impossibility of installing a child seat
inability to securely fasten a child seat
inadequate seat belt design or functionality
lack of proper anchorage points for child seats.
